From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ArcBoost Builder <build@arcboost.local>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 22:10:59 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 06/13] ArcBoost: circular_feature, circular_period,
 max_bin_circular config
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds three new Config parameters:

  - circular_feature: list of feature indices/names to treat as circular,
    mirroring the existing categorical_feature parameter syntax (including
    the name:col1,col2 prefix form). Per-feature period overrides via
    name:wind_dir=360,phase=6.283 syntax are supported (parsing handled by
    a follow-up patch in src/io/config_*.cpp).
  - circular_period: default period for circular features. Defaults to 2*pi
    (radians); common alternatives are 360 (degrees), 24 (hour-of-day),
    365.25 (day-of-year).
  - max_bin_circular: max number of arc-bins per circular feature, default
    64. Kept lower than max_bin (255) because arc-search is O(B^2); raise
    toward 255 if higher angular resolution matters more than split-find
    time.

Pure declaration patch — the parsing logic for the per-feature period
override syntax lives in src/io/config_*.cpp and is added separately.
---
 include/LightGBM/config.h | 22 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 22 insertions(+)

diff --git a/include/LightGBM/config.h b/include/LightGBM/config.h
index 208f6bc6..d7607684 100644
--- a/include/LightGBM/config.h
+++ b/include/LightGBM/config.h
@@ -791,6 +791,28 @@ struct Config {
   // desc = **Note**: floating point numbers in categorical features will be rounded towards 0
   std::string categorical_feature = "";
 
+  // ArcBoost: circular feature support.
+  // type = multi-int or string
+  // alias = arc_feature, circular_column, arc_column, circular_features
+  // desc = used to specify circular features (features whose domain is a circle, e.g. wind direction, hour-of-day, day-of-year, phase angles)
+  // desc = use number for index, e.g. ``circular_feature=0,3`` means column\_0 and column\_3 are circular features
+  // desc = add a prefix ``name:`` for column name, e.g. ``circular_feature=name:wind_dir,phase`` means wind_dir and phase are circular features
+  // desc = per-feature period override syntax: ``circular_feature=name:wind_dir=360,phase=6.283185307179586`` (defaults to ``circular_period`` if omitted)
+  // desc = circular features are split as arcs ``[a, b] mod period`` rather than linear thresholds
+  std::string circular_feature = "";
+
+  // ArcBoost: default period for circular features when not specified per-feature.
+  // desc = default period for circular features (overridable per-feature in ``circular_feature``)
+  // desc = ``2*pi`` (≈ 6.283) for radians, ``360`` for degrees, ``24`` for hour-of-day, ``365.25`` for day-of-year
+  double circular_period = 6.283185307179586;
+
+  // ArcBoost: max number of arc-bins for circular features.
+  // desc = max number of bins for circular features
+  // desc = lower than ``max_bin`` (255) by default since arc-search is O(B^2) and 64 bins gives ~5.6 degree resolution at period 2pi
+  // desc = raise toward 255 for higher angular resolution at the cost of split-find time
+  // check = >1
+  int max_bin_circular = 64;
+
   // desc = path to a ``.json`` file that specifies bin upper bounds for some or all features
   // desc = ``.json`` file should contain an array of objects, each containing the word ``feature`` (integer feature index) and ``bin_upper_bound`` (array of thresholds for binning)
   // desc = see `this file <https://github.com/microsoft/LightGBM/blob/master/examples/regression/forced_bins.json>`__ as an example
